article.headline: Ruot Bijiek and Elvin Edmonds IV each score 12 points as Bucknell beats Lafayette 60-50
article.description: — Ruot Bijiek and Elvin Edmonds IV each scored 12 points to lead Bucknell over Lafayette 60-50 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Ruot Bijiek and Elvin Edmonds IV each score 12 points as Bucknell beats Lafayette 60-50
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- — Ruot Bijiek and Elvin Edmonds IV each scored 12 points to lead Bucknell over Lafayette 60-50 on Saturday night. Bijiek had six rebounds for the Bison (13-18, 10-8 Patriot League). Edmonds added six assists. Josh Bascoe finished with nine points. Kyle Jenkins finished with 12 points and seven rebounds for the Leopards (11-20, 10-8). Lafayette also got 12 points and three steals from Eric Sondberg. In addition, Devin Hines had eight points and six rebounds. Bucknell used an 11-2 second-half run to come back from a five-point deficit and take the lead at 52-48 with 2:59 remaining. Edmonds scored 10 second-half points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
